    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-12-03T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-12-03T05:00:00-05:00" n="96"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d96">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">892.00–FA/12–351: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Thailand</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Turner</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bangkok</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-12-03T17:00:00+07:00"
                            >December 3, 1951—5 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1246. We believe point 3 para 1 of draft note contained in Dept’s A–184, Nov 23,
                    wld be misunderstood by Thais and agreement thus made more difficult. More
                    important reason for removing point 3 from draft is strong probability that its
                    inclusion wld tend to confirm Commie claims that US mil and econ aid is in
                    return for full Thai coop in “aggressive US mil intentions” and wld support
                    arguments of those here who profess fear of mil domination by US.</p>
                <p>Emb is consequently proceeding with negots on basis of draft from which point 3
                    has been dropped. Progress will be reported.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Turner</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
